This paper addresses the task of Unsupervised Video Object Segmentation (UVOS) using a novel algorithm that combines segmentation and tracking. The paper heavily relies on computer vision techniques such as decision forests and spatio-temporal consistency, which are commonly used in the computer vision community. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper introduces a novel data association algorithm, which involves machine learning techniques such as decision forests, and optimization techniques such as path cutting. Therefore, the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also evaluates its approach on a video segmentation dataset, which falls under the multimedia subfield, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on tracking objects in a video sequence may also make it relevant to the robotics community, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category.
